<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1990-03-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Intravenous Fluid Therapy in Calves</TITLE><BODY>Effective intravenous fluid therapy requires determination of the volume required and the composition of the appropriate parenteral solution. Specific abnormalities in major electrolytes, acid-base balance, and energy balance should be considered in fluid selection. Parenteral solutions should be delivered in a sterile manner, with attention to potential complications.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>